# Currency display — Toman (layer 2 only)

**Layer 2 only.** FX (Stars, USDT, rates) → `currency-fx-boundaries.mdc`. Never mix layer 2 and 3 in one commit/PR.

## Rules

| OK | Forbidden |
|----|-----------|
| `settings.format_price` / `texts.format_price` | `TELEGRAM_STARS_RATE_*`, `kopeks_to_rubles` in same task |
| `PRICE_DISPLAY_SUFFIX` (`تومان`), `apply_price_display_symbol` | Rename `*_kopeks` columns/fields |
| `{price}` from formatter in locales | New `₽` in user-facing strings |
| Same integer in balance vs missing-amount UI | Ad-hoc `/100` or multiply in handlers |
| bot + cabinet + miniapp together | Changing webhook/provider amounts |

## Factor 1 (UX)

Stored integer = **Toman unit** for the user. Names (`price_kopeks`, DB columns) do not matter for display work.

## `format_price` / divmod(100)

If changing display scaling, use a **dedicated** commit (e.g. `fix(currency): unify format_price display unit`) and price smoke — **not** in the same commit as Stars/crypto FX.

## Smoke (user)

Top-up, purchase, or C2C card line: amounts show **تومان** only; balance vs “missing” amounts stay consistent.
